parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Third Gear Failure in Yamaha Motorcycles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the third gear in Yamaha motorcycles can cause the transmission to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injury or death.
symptoms: Loud whining or grinding noises when shifting into or out of third gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, leaving the rider vulnerable to accidents or injuries, especially when stopping in traffic or navigating through intersections.
symptoms: The engine stalls when stopping in traffic or idling
the vehicle stalls when the brake pedal is depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump housing can cause unpredictable jerking and stalling of the engine, leading to a loss of vehicle control, increased risk of accidents, and potential serious injury or death.
symptoms: The engine jerks or stalls suddenly
causing loss of power and control
and potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
